When choosing a repository to be cloned, if the given local destination directory does not exist the following error message is displayed:

{color:#ff0000}Invalid clone path. Folder must be exist and also be empty.{color}

{color:#000000}Which should, of course, instead say:{color}

{color:#ff0000}Invalid clone path. Folder must exist and also be empty.{color}

I tried to attach a screenshot of the page but the issue creator kept giving me this error message: JIRA could not attach the file as there was a missing token. Please try attaching the file again. I don't know what that means but I tried several times and it never worked, so hopefully using the embed tool in the WYSIWYG editor worked:

!image-2017-11-23-20-07-22-563.png!

If the screenshot wasn't embedded correctly I also uploaded it to Imgur: [https://i.imgur.com/sHOz1hJ.png]

Edit: I think I got the image to attach but I'm not really sure. This is a confusing WYSIWYG editor.

*I'd like to push to a new remote which needs a 2nd SSH key.*

So I added a `.ssh/config`
{code:java}
Host gasag bitbucket.org
    HostName bitbucket.org
    IdentityFile ~/.ssh/id_rsa_gamma
    User itsme{code}
 Now I can push on terminal
 {color:#d4d4d4}itsme@Machine MINGW32 ~/Projects/Gamma.TheProject (master){color}
 {color:#d4d4d4}$ git push gamma master{color}
 {color:#d4d4d4}Everything up-to-date{color}
----
If I try this on Sourcetree:
{noformat}
git -c diff.mnemonicprefix=false -c core.quotepath=false push -v --set-upstream gamma master:master
Pushing to git@bitbucket.org:gammade/theproject.git
repository access denied.
fatal: Could not read from remote repository.

Please make sure you have the correct access rights
and the repository exists.

Completed with errors, see above.{noformat}
Note: I've added both (my main and my new) SSH keys

!image-2017-11-08-11-49-30-770.png!
